cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper deals with the problem of compositional generalization in sequence-to-sequence learning, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel approach using memory-augmented neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of meta-learning, which is a popular topic in both cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses the SCAN dataset, which involves visual input, suggesting a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
